    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="1780"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1780">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.74/55a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Price</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 13, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>On account of the war in Europe and the possibility of the Canal Zone being drawn
                    into the sphere of active operations, it is absolutely essential that the United
                    States exercise immediate monopoly of all wireless stations in the Republic of
                    Panama and control the radio equipment of all ships in the territorial waters of
                    Panama.</p>
                <p>You are instructed to bring the importance of this matter to the attention of the
                    Minister for Foreign Affairs and to request that the Panaman Government issue
                    immediate orders in this sense.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
